Six people were killed when a small plane crashed in eastern Zimbabwe near the border with Mozambique, a state-owned newspaper said on Tuesday. The Mozambican-registered eight-seater plane crashed into the Vumba mountains near the Mozambican boarder, with witnesses blaming bad weather, The Herald newspaper said. Four of the people were directors of a Mozambican company that has operations in Zimbabwe, while the two crew members were a father and son. The Herald said an aid force helicopter had airlifted the bodies to a nearby hospital. ALSO READ: Zimbabwe police out in force ahead of opposition protest